topics.body:
Even if Gawker loses even a fraction of the amount they're getting sued for Gawker legitimately does not save enough money to keep afloat.

Let's say they only lose $10million; they would have to sell the company.

No matter what at this point Gawker is going to have to be sold to someone else for cheap.  It's legitimately game over for Gawker network cause no matter what happens at this point someone is going to buy them out and "Gawker" is going to be sold.  Sure they'll continue as a business, *BUT* chances are they're going to be bought out by a large company and forced to change drastically as a business from the ground up cause someone else will own them.
